item.description:
NOTE: Due to a conflict, we won't be starting until 1 p.m. (although you should be able to get into the building by 12:30 p.m.)

This month's activity will be origami with Kate Robinson. You will learn how to do some 2-D origami that you will be able to use on ATCs. Please bring any papers you'd like to use, and extra paper cutters would be appreciated. 

This month's swap themes: #1: Favorite song or song lyrics. #2: Technique swap: Stamp collages (use 2 or more stamps or layer stamps on cards).
item.how_to_find_us: Details in e-mails sent to everyone who RSVPs "yes;" also posted on Message Board
item.why: We want to create and play and learn and share and have a great time doing it.
